The set $\{ \phi_{Llm},\phi_{Llm}^*, \; L>0 \}\bigcup\{ \phi_0 \}$ forms a pseudo-orthonormal basis for this Krein space, for which the non-vanishing inner products are
\begin{eqnarray}\label{Kreininner} \langle \phi_{Llm, L>0},\phi_{Llm, L>0} \rangle &=& \langle \phi_0,\phi_0 \rangle=1, {\nonumber}\\
\langle \phi^*_{Llm, L>0},\phi^*_{Llm, L>0} \rangle &=& \langle \phi^*_0,\phi^*_0 \rangle=-1. \end{eqnarray}
Through this construction, the space ${\cal{H}}$ contains non-physical states including negative norm states, but not restricted to them ($\psi_s \notin {\cal{K}}$ and so $\phi_0 \notin {\cal{K}}$ the space of physical states). Nevertheless, considering the non-physical states, as intermediate objects, are remarkably inevitable to guarantee the de Sitter and the gauge covariance of the theory.

